content: Great app. Nice to have a self-hosted feed that I can access on my phone!
Is it possible if you have the app on two devices they will sync with each other?
replyContent: If you are done reading the news on phone 1, you can manually synchronize with the nextcloud server. On phone 2 you can trigger a sync as well - this way both devices will have the same unread and starred items. You can also enable auto-sync on startup to make this easier.

content: An awesome reader, using it for years. Keep up the great work.
replyContent: Thank you very much for the great feedback! Glad you are enjoying the app for such a long period of time!

content: Great app

App was crashing making it unusable after updating to 0.9.9.36 (Not sure if this is the last version cause this as I'm not too often was using it). Everything was sorted after I uninstalled the app and installed it again and synced the news feed.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback and sorry about the inconveniences. Glad it's working again!

content: Good! Mimics the browser app nicely! Not sure if I'm experiencing a bug or a feature though: I can't view read articles at all. All of my news sources are rss feeds, and after I've read them, they are gone forever, it seems. Edit: I was expecting an experience closer to the browser app (where read articles stay for as long as they are in the rss feed), but that was an incorrect assumtion. I'll get into the habit of starring items I want to read (or re-read) later. Thanks for clearing that up!
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback! That is correct, your unread feeds will disappear after you have read them. If you want them to stay (to read them later) please mark them as unread or use the "star" option. Both will make the item stay on your phone. Short explanation: We need to remove items since the database on your phone can't store that much data.

content: Fantastic app, but recent change to the way articles are being displayed is a no-go for me ;( I used to have articles topics [and nothing more] configured  to be displayed with one of the display option, but now none of these option seem to do that, with one, max two lines of the topic and nothing more.  Is there a way to re-add it to the app as a separate option? I've got TONS of RSS channels and scrolling them with details beneath a topic is a pain and takes much more time :/
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback. The upcoming beta (release is tomorrow) will reintroduce a "headlines" view again. I hope you'll like it! Feel free to open an issue on GitHub if you have more suggestions on how to improve the app.

content: If you have access to a OwnCloud (or NextCloud) server and can install the OC News app on it (no particular technical skill required), that setup in combination with this Android app is a terrific way to read lots of news feeds. I'm using it now in combination with NextCloud v10, and it works like a charm. The Android apps even zooms non-mobile ready sites properly in the browser window so it is easier to read them. I use this app everyday on a HTC One phone and an Asus tablet.
My only complaint is that the widget doesn't auto refresh. Other than that, pretty good.
Bought expecting a widget (because the description states so), but ...no widget. Otherwise, great.
Update: dev was able to fix my issue!  Reddit feeds and imgur pages seem buggy and I often have to jump into an external browser on nexus 5, 7(2013), 9/Android 6.0.1
replyContent: Thanks for the report. I just tested some Reddit and Imgur feeds but it's working fine. Do you have some sample feeds for me? Please contact me via email at david-dev@live.de or file an issue on github! Thanks in advance!

content: Thanks for this great app. I use it daily.  Sync even works reliably with my home server (slowest ADSL money can buy,  dynamic IP address,  non-standard port,  self signed certificate).

replyContent: Please send me an email with your server setup. If you're using a self-signed certificate make sure that you've allowed self signed certs in the login dialog. And please make sure that the url is correct.
